# support losses are because he is a c*tholic

Konrad Adenauer, the long-time Mayor of Cologne, has been elevated to the leadership of one of Germany's largest parties, which he strongly supported the formation of. Adenauer is committed to democratic principles and sits on the right wing of the former <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>, without being tied to Christian labor. This has granted him the ability to rally a broad coalition of party leaders around his calm and stabilizing leadership against the more fringe politicians of the party.

With his slogan 'No Experiments!', we do not expect any major changes to the party program under his leadership, fostering a sense among the people that the <span style="color: #000000;">**[+ z_party_name +]**</span> is a pole of stability that the German people can rally behind. In terms of our relationship with the <span style="color: #000000;">Christians</span>, Adenauer, being a former <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span> member, is relatively more friendly toward us than many others to his right. We can also count on the pressure from the <span style="color: #FF7F00;">Christian Left</span>, who, similar to the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s left wing historically, are powerless to enact changes to the left but are influential in preventing changes to the right.

