A key figure of the German Right since the Republic's inception, Kuno von Westarp has ascended to the leadership role of the colossal <span style="color: #000000;">Christian People's Party</span>—certainly a significant step up. His election was primarily driven by the unified support of the entire former <span style="color: #3E88B3;">nationalist</span> faction within the party.

Westarp is highly experienced in managing internal dissent and is careful not to lean too heavily into any one particular wing of the party, aiming to avoid fracturing the organization. While the party program remains largely unchanged, there has been a noticeable increase in antisemitic and pro-monarchist rhetoric, as Westarp seeks to preserve the character of the now-defunct <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> within this new entity.

It goes without saying, Westarp's leadership will make cooperation within the party impossible for the foreseeable future.

